ble Bottom}}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! Country\n! Date\n! Format\n! Label\n! {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| February 8, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| {{hlist|[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]|Robot and Human}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/id/album/death-bed-feat-beabadoobee-coffee-for-your-head-single/1498128757|title=death bed (feat. beabadoobee) [coffee for your head] - Single by Powfu on Apple Music|via=[[Apple Music]]|date=February 8, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| April 7, 2020\n| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| Columbia\n| <ref name=\"AllAccess\">{{cite web|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|website=All Access|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330200214/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=March 31, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of number-one songs of 2020 (Malaysia)]]\n*[[List of number-one songs of 2020 (Singapore)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:TikTok songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Singapore]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 single by Powfu featuring Beabadoobee}}\n{{Other uses|Deathbed (disambiguation){{!}}Deathbed}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Death Bed\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Powfu - Death Bed.png\n| alt        =\n| artist     = [[Powfu]] featuring [[Beabadoobee]]\n| album      =\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   = 2019\n| released   = <!-- Commercial release date, not SoundCloud upload date -->{{start date|2020|02|08|mf=y}}\n| genre      = [[Lo-fi hip hop]]<!-- Sourced in prose -->\n| length     = {{duration|m=2|s=53}}\n| label      = [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Powfu|Isaiah Faber]]\n* [[Beabadoobee|Beatrice Laus]]\n* Oscar Lang\n| producer   = Otterpop\n| chronology = [[Beabadoobee]]\n| prev_title = I Wish I Was Stephen Malkmus\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|jJPMnTXl63E|\"Death Bed\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Death Bed'''\", later re-titled as \"'''Death Bed (Coffee for Your Head)'''\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/track/7eJMfftS33KTjuF7lTsMCx|title=\"death bed (coffee for your head) (feat. beabadoobee)\" on Spotify}}</ref> (stylized in [[Letter case#All lowercase|all lowercase]]) is a song by Canadian rapper [[Powfu]], featuring Filipino-British singer-songwriter [[Beabadoobee]]. The song was initially uploaded to [[SoundCloud]] in 2019; following Powfu signing to [[Columbia Records]], the song was released on streaming services on February 8, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/powfu-breaks-down-the-meaning-of-death-bed|title=Powfu Breaks Down The Meaning Of \"Death Bed\"|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last=Reneau|first=Steven|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref> The song samples the 2017 song \"Coffee\" by Beabadoobee, who is credited as a feature.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/08/powfu-beabadoobees-death-bed-picks-up-pop-radio-airplay-reaches-50-million-spotify-streams/|title=Powfu & Beabadoobee's \"Death Bed\" Picks Up Pop Radio Airplay, Reaches 50 Million Spotify Streams|website=Headline Planet|last=Cantor|first=Brian|date=March 8, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe song went viral on the video sharing app [[TikTok]] in early 2020.<ref name=\"Genius BG\">{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/powfu-s-death-bed-samples-beabadoobee-s-coffee|title=Powfu's Viral Hit \"Death Bed\" Arrives On Streaming Services After Lengthy Sample Clearance Delay|website=Genius|last=Fu|first=Eddie|date=February 13, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThe song's commercial release was delayed by a year due to the clearance of the [[Sampling (music)|sample]] of Beabadoobee's 2017 song \"Coffee\". Powfu said on [[Twitter]] in April 2019 that he had not put it on [[Spotify]] because he was \"scared [he'd] get in trouble from the sample [he] use[s] in it\", but said he \"would upload it anyway\" and told his followers to give him \"a week and a half\". It was finally released to streaming and download services in February 2020.<ref name=\"Genius BG\"/>\n\n==Composition==\nColumbia's British subsidiary [[Sony Music UK]] described it as a \"lo-fi hip hop single\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/sonymusicuk/view/205330/|title=Powfu \u2013 New Single 'Death Bed' Feat Beabadoobee Out Now|publisher=[[Sony Music UK]]|via=[[Pressparty]]|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| 5\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|11|artist=Powfu feat. Beabadoobee|song=Death Bed|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|7|artist=Powfu feat. Beabadoobee|song=Death Bed|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 24, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|46|artist=Powfu feat. Beabadoobee|song=Death Bed|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|16|artist=Beabadoobee|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|10|year=2020|week=16|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=13&